\n|elevation_max_ft           =\n|elevation_min_m            =\n|elevation_min_ft           =\n<!-- Population   ----------------------->\n|population_as_of               =\n|population_footnotes           =\n|population_note                =\n|population_total               = \n|population_density_km2         = <!--For automatic calculation, any density field may contain: auto -->\n|population_density_sq_mi       =\n<!-- General information  --------------->\n|timezone               = [[Pakistan Standard Time|PST]]\n|utc_offset             = +5\n|timezone_DST           = [[Pakistan Standard Time|PST (DST)]]\n|utc_offset_DST         = +6\n|coor_pinpoint         =<!-- can be used to specify exactly where/what the coordinates refer to -->\n|coordinates            = {{Coord|30|33|0|N|72|7|58|E|type:city_region:PK|display=inline,title}}\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n|postal_code_type       =  <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n|postal_code            =\n|area_code              = 06524\n|website                =\n|footnotes              =\n\n}}\n'''Abdul Hakeem''' (also known as '''Abdul Hakim'''), ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|'''\u0639\u0628\u062f\u064f\u0627\u0644\u062d\u06a9\u0650\u06cc\u0645 '''}}}}), is a city in [[Kabirwala Tehsil]], [[Khanewal District]] in the [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]] province of [[Pakistan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nrb.gov.pk/lg_election/union.asp?district=16&dn=Khanewal|title=Tehsils & Unions in the District of Khanewal|publisher=National Reconstruction Bureau, Government of Pakistan|accessdate=9 November 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110807200017/http://www.nrb.gov.pk/lg_election/union.asp?district=16&dn=Khanewal|archive-date=7 August 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Location ===\nThe city is situated 10 kilometres from [[Tulamba]] and is 3&nbsp;km from the Ravi River<ref>[http://www.fallingrain.com/world/PK/04/Abdul_Hakim.html Location of Abdul Hakim \u2013 Falling Rain Genomics]</ref> and 28&nbsp;km from [[Mian Channu]]. The tomb of Saint Abdul Hakeem is located in the city centre near Multan road.\n\n== Famous events ==\nThe famous event in the city is the yearly [[Urs]] of the Saint Abdul Hakeem, held every year from June 21 to 23. Thousands of the followers of the saint visit the tomb, and a Grand Lok [[Mela]] and the [[List of circuses and circus owners|Lucky Irani Circus]] take place during the [[Urs]].\n\nColleges and schools\n\nAbdul Hakeem has schools and colleges including [[ Dar-e-Arqam Schools|Dare Arqam school]], [[Allied Schools (Pakistan)|Allied School]], [[Army Public Schools & Colleges System|Army Public School]]. The City has [[High schools]] for girls and boys and a [[Degree college]] for both genders. There is also a [[Vocational training]] centre for boys and girls. \n\n== Emergency medical services ==\nIn Abdul Hakeem City, is a rural health center run by the Government of Punjab,<ref>[https://punjab.gov.pk/node/908 RHC, Abdul Hakeem Health centre]</ref> and some private clinics, these clinics have the facility of many medical services e.g. dialysis, operations and gynaecology.\n\n== History ==\nAbdul Hakeem is also one of the historical city in the region. The city is named after Sufi Saint of Silsila Qadria descent Hazrat Sultan Abdul Hakim (R.A) who came to this place, settled here. The shrine of Sultan Abdul Hakeem is located in the start of City. The city is more 300 years old.\n\n==Notable people==\n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666 Only add a person to this list if they already have their own article on the English Wikipedia \u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666 Please keep the list in alphabetical order by LAST NAME \u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n*[[Rana Asif Saeed]] Advocate, Ex Member [[Punjab Bar Council]].\n\n== Economy ==\nImportant in the city is a 450 MW Rousch thermal power plant working at Sidhnai Barrage in Abdul Hakeem.<ref>[http://www.rouschpak.com Rousch Pakistan]</ref> The city has an old head-work on the historical river Ravi, and a canal named Fazil Shah and a small link canal that are used for irrigation.\n\nThe city has the one out of the 3 railway station situated in [[Kabirwala Tehsil]], which is named 'Abdul Hakim', other 2 are named as #Dirkhana and 'Jan Muhammad Wala', while the other 3 Tehsils of [[Khanewal District|Khanewal]] have one railway station each.\n\nThe population of the city depends on agriculture, and there are wheat\u060c rice and cotton factories and flour mills in the city.\n\n== Politics ==\nThe residents of this city do not adhere to any one political party. Every new election here is won by a different party.\n\n== Transport ==\nThe latest development in the city is the junction interchange of the two motorways by [[China\u2013Pakistan Economic Corridor|CPEC]], [[M3 motorway (Pakistan)|M3]] (Lahore) & [[M4 motorway (Pakistan)|M4 (]][[Pindi Bhattian]]) which will merge the two motorways and will lead to [[Shujabad]] near [[Multan]] and connect to [[M5 motorway (Pakistan)|M5]] which will lead further to [[Sukkur]] ([[M6 motorway (Pakistan)|M6]]).\n\nThe Abdul Hakeem inter change on the Lahore Abdul Hakeem Motorway leads the traffic to [[Lahore]] and [[Islamabad]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{navboxes| title = Nearby cities\n| state = collapsed\n| list1  = \n; Throughout the district\n{{Geographic location|Centre=Abdul Hakeem|North=''[[River Ravi]]'' {{convert|3|km|mi|abbr=on}}|Northeast=|East=[[Tulamba]] {{convert|11|km|mi|abbr=on}}|Southeast=[[Mian Channu]] {{convert|24|km|mi|abbr=on}}|South=Kacha Khuh {{convert|20|km|mi|abbr=on}}|Southwest=[[Khanewal]] {{convert|33|km|mi|abbr=on}}|West=[[Kabirwala]] {{convert|30|km|mi|abbr=on}}|Northwest=}}\n\n; Throughout Punjab Province\n{{Geographic location|Centre=Abdul Hakeem|North=|Northeast=|East=|Southeast=|South=[[Mailsi]] {{convert|83|km|mi|abbr=on}}|Southwest=|West=}}\n\n; Throughout Pakistan\n{{Geographic location|Centre=Abdul Hakeem|North=|Northeast=|East=|Southeast=|South=|Southwest=|West=|Northwest=}}\n}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Khanewal District]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=October 2012}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2012}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n|name                   = Abdul Hakeem\n|official_name          = \n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = <br />{{Nastaliq|'''\u0639\u0628\u062f\u064f\u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0650\u064a\u0645'''}}<!-- if different from the English name -->\n|translit_lang1         = <!-- [[Urdu]] -->\n|translit_lang1_type    = <!-- [[Perso-Arabic script]] -->\n|translit_lang1_info    =\n|nickname               =\n|settlement_type        = [[City]]<!-- e.g. Town, Village, City, etc.-->\n|total_type             = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n|motto                  =\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->\n|image_skyline          = Railway St Abdulhakeem.jpg\n|imagesize              =\n|image_caption          = [[Abdul Hakim railway station]]\n|image_flag             = <!-- This image is non-free. 100px-Pk-punj.PNG -->\n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             =\n|seal_size              =\n|image_shield           =\n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     =\n|blank_emblem_type      =\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map              = \n|mapsize                =\n|map_caption            =\n|image_map1             =\n|mapsize1               =\n|map_caption1           =\n|image_dot_map          =\n|dot_mapsize            =\n|dot_map_caption        =\n|dot_x =  |dot_y =\n|pushpin_map            = Punjab Pakistan#Pakistan<!-- the name of a location map as per http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Location_map -->\n|pushpin_label_position = bottom<!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_map_caption    =\n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n<!-- Locatio