{"title_page": "Saddar Town", "text_new": "{{Use Pakistani English|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}{{about||the neighbourhood and commercial district|Saddar}}{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->| name                            = Saddar Town<br> {{nq|\u0635\u062f\u0631 \u0679\u0627\u0624\u0646}}\n| settlement_type                 = [[Towns in Karachi|Town of Karachi]]\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->| image_skyline                   = File:SaddarTown Karachi.PNG\n| image_caption                   = Saddar Town was divided into 11 Union Councils\n| image_flag                      = \n| image_seal                      = \n| image_map                       = \n| map_caption                     = <!-- Location ------------------>\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[Pakistan]]\n| subdivision_type1               = Province\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Sindh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = City District\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Karachi]]\n| parts_type                      = Union Councils\n| parts_style                     = coll,para\n| parts                           = 11\n| p1                              = [[City Railway Colony]]<br>[[Civil Line]]<br>[[Clifton, Karachi|Clifton]]<br>[[Garden (Karachi)|Garden]]<br>[[Gazdarabad]]<br>\n[[Islam Pura]]/[[Millat Nagar]]<br>[[Kharadar]]<br>[[Kehkashan (Karachi)|Khehkashan]]<br>[[Nanak Wara]]<br>[[Old Haji Camp]]<br>[[Cantt]] \n<!-- Politics ----------------->| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = Town Council\n| leader_title                    = Town Nazim\n| leader_name                     = Muhammad Dilawar\n| leader_title1                   = Naib Nazim\n| leader_name1                    = \n| leader_title2                   = Municipal Officer\n| leader_name2                    = \n| established_title               = Established\n| established_date                = 2001\n<!-- Population   ----------------------->| population_as_of                = 1998\n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = 616,151\n<!-- General information  --------------->\n\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->| postal_code_type                = <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = \n| website                         = [http://125.209.91.254/CDGK/LinkClick.aspx?link=211&tabid=72 Saddar Town Page]\n| official_name                   = \n| extinct_title                   = Disbanded\n| extinct_date                    = 2011\n}}\n\n'''Saddar Town'''  ({{lang-sd|'''\u0635\u062f\u0631 \u067d\u0627\u0626\u0648\u0646'''}}; {{lang-ur|{{nq|'''\u0635\u062f\u0631 \u0679\u0627\u0624\u0646'''}}}}), was a [[Towns in Karachi|Karachi borough]] in the central part of the city that formed much of the historic colonial core of [[Karachi]]. Saddar Town was formed in 2001 as part of the [https://web.archive.org/web/20081013065059/http://www.nrb.gov.pk/city_district/index.html The Local Government Ordinance 2001], and was subdivided into 11 [[Union councils of Pakistan|Union Councils]]. The Town system and was disbanded in 2011,<ref>{{Cite book|last=Gayer|first=Laurent|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BklRBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA156&lpg=PA156&dq=karachi+towns+disbanded+2011&source=bl&ots=a0EX8EYYqr&sig=ACfU3U1ZiUfKRKtF9CzZQ7yMEaA8aAfgPg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwir4qiZ--3oAhXjK30KHRWgDCsQ6AEwAnoECA8QKA#v=onepage&q=karachi%20towns%20disbanded%202011&f=false|title=Karachi: Ordered Disorder and the Struggle for the City|date=2014|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-935444-3|language=en}}</ref> and Saddar Town was re-organized as part of [[Karachi South District]] in 2015.\n\n==Etymology==\nThe word ''Saddar'' generally means the \"centre\" (of a settlement) and also \"head\" (of a group of people or an organisation). \n\n==Location==\nSaddar is located in the colonial heart of Karachi. It is bordered by [[Jamshed Town]] and [[Clifton Cantonment]] to the east, [[Kiamari Town]] and the [[Arabian Sea]] to the south and [[Lyari Town]] to the west. The majority of the population are [[Gujarati people|Gujarati]] and [[Sindhi people|Sindhi]] Muslims. Among the Gujarati-speaking people are trading communities such as [[Memon people|Memon]]s and [[Marwari people|Marwari]]s.<ref name=\"Dawn\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/150906|title=KARACHI: Saddar: the VIP town|date=5 August 2005|publisher=Dawn (newspaper)|accessdate=7 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nSaddar Town contained much of the oldest parts of Karachi.  The federal government under [[Pervez Musharraf]], who seized power in a [[1999 Pakistani coup d'\u00e9tat|1999 coup d'etat]], introduced local government reforms in the year 2000, which eliminated the previous \"third tier of government\" ([[Divisions of Pakistan|administrative divisions]]) and replaced it with the fourth tier ([[Districts of Pakistan|districts]]). The effect in Karachi was the dissolution of the former [[Karachi Division]], and the merging of its five districts to form a new Karachi City-District with eighteen autonomous constituent towns including Saddar Town. In 2011, the system was disbanded but remained in place for bureaucratic administration until 2015, when the [[Karachi Metropolitan Corporation]] system was reintroduced. In 2015, Saddar Town was re-organized as part of [[Karachi South]].\n\n== Neighbourhoods ==\nSaddar Town was made up of the following:\n\n{|cellspacing=\"6\"\n|-\n|\n* [[Bath Island]]\n* [[Clifton (Karachi)|Clifton]]\n* [[City Railway Colony]]\n* [[Civil Lines]]\n* [[Garden (Karachi)|Garden]]<ref name=Dawn/>\n* [[Gazdarabad]]\n* [[Islam Pura]]\n* [[Kalakot]]\n* [[Kehkashan]]\n* [[Kharadar]]<ref name=Dawn/>\n|\n* [[Ghanchi Para]]<ref name=Dawn/>\n* [[Millat Nagar]]\n* [[Nanak Wara]]<ref name=Dawn/>\n* [[Narayan Pura]]\n* [[Old Haji Camp]]\n* [[Ranchore Line]]\n* [[Saddar]]\n* Staff Lines Cantt\n* Iqbal Lines Cantt\n* Army Officers Mess\n* Jinnah Lines Cantt\n* Umerkot Lines Cantt\n* Askari-I Cantt\n* Askari-II Cantt\n* Askari-III Cantt\n* Com Kar Cantt\n* Abdul Sattar Edhi Hockey Stadium Cantt\n* [[Shah Rasool Colony]]\n* [[Sikanderabad (Karachi)|Sikanderabad]]\n* [[Shireen Jinnah Colony]]\n|}\n\n<gallery>\n</gallery>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[City District Government]]\n* [[Karachi]]\n* [[Lahore]]\n*[[Sindh Baloch Cooperative Housing Society]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.karachicity.gov.pk Karachi Website]\n* [https://archive.is/20121128182904/http://14.192.147.139/cdgk/Home/Towns/GulshanTown/tabid/211/townid/6/default.aspx Saddar Town]\n\n\n\n{{Karachi Towns}}\n{{Karachi topics}}\n\n{{coord|24|51|27|N|67|00|10|E|region:PK_type:city_source:kolossus-ruwiki|display=title}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Saddar Town}}\n[[Category:Saddar Town| ]]\n[[Category:Neighbourhoods of Karachi]]\n[[Category:Clifton, Karachi]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Pakistani English|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}{{about||the neighbourhood and commercial district|Saddar}}{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->| name                            = Saddar Town<br> {{nq|\u0635\u062f\u0631 \u0679\u0627\u0624\u0646}}\n| settlement_type                 = [[Towns in Karachi|Borough of Karachi]]\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->| image_skyline                   = File:SaddarTown Karachi.PNG\n| image_caption                   = Saddar Town was divided into 11 Union Councils\n| image_flag                      = \n| image_seal                      = \n| image_map                       = \n| map_caption                     = <!-- Location ------------------>\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[Pakistan]]\n| subdivision_type1               = Province\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Sindh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = City District\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Karachi]]\n| parts_type                      = Union Councils\n| parts_style                     = coll,para\n| parts                           = 11\n| p1                              = [[City Railway Colony]]<br>[[Civil Line]]<br>[[Clifton, Karachi|Clifton]]<br>[[Garden (Karachi)|Garden]]<br>[[Gazdarabad]]<br>\n[[Islam Pura]]/[[Millat Nagar]]<br>[[Kharadar]]<br>[[Kehkashan (Karachi)|Khehkashan]]<br>[[Nanak Wara]]<br>[[Old Haji Camp]]<br>[[Cantt]] \n<!-- Politics ----------------->| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = Town Council\n| leader_title                    = Town Nazim\n| leader_name                     = Muhammad Dilawar\n| leader_title1                   = Naib Nazim\n| leader_name1                    = \n| leader_title2                   = Municipal Officer\n| leader_name2                    = \n| established_title               = Established\n| established_date                = 2001\n<!-- Population   ----------------------->| population_as_of                = 1998\n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = 616,151\n<!-- General information  --------------->\n\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->| postal_code_type                = <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = \n| website                         = [http://125.209.91.254/CDGK/LinkClick.aspx?link=211&tabid=72 Saddar Town Page]\n| official_name                   = \n| extinct_title                   = Disbanded\n| extinct_date                    = 2011\n}}\n\n'''Saddar Town'''  ({{lang-sd|'''\u0635\u062f\u0631 \u067d\u0627\u0626\u0648\u0646'''}}; {{lang-ur|{{nq|'''\u0635\u062f\u0631 \u0679\u0627\u0624\u0646'''}}}}), was a [[Towns in Karachi|Karachi borough]] in the central part of the city that formed much of the historic colonial core of [[Karachi]]. Saddar Town was formed in 2001 as part of the [https://web.archive.org/web/20081013065059/http://www.nrb.gov.pk/city_district/index.html The Local Government Ordinance 2001], and was subdivided into 11 [[Union councils of Pakistan|Union Councils]]. The Town system and was disbanded in 2011,<ref>{{Cite book|last=Gayer|first=Laurent|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BklRBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA156&lpg=PA156&dq=karachi+towns+disbanded+2011&source=bl&ots=a0EX8EYYqr&sig=ACfU3U1ZiUfKRKtF9CzZQ7yMEaA8aAfgPg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwir4qiZ--3oAhXjK30KHRWgDCsQ6AEwAnoECA8QKA#v=onepage&q=karachi%20towns%20disbanded%202011&f=false|title=Karachi: Ordered Disorder and the Struggle for the City|date=2014|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-935444-3|language=en}}</ref> and Saddar Town was re-organized as part of [[Karachi South]] in 2015.\n\n==Etymology==\nThe word ''Saddar'' generally means the \"centre\" (of a settlement) and also \"head\" (of a group of people or an organisation). \n\n==Location==\nSaddar is located in the colonial heart of Karachi. It is bordered by [[Jamshed Town]] and [[Clifton Cantonment]] to the east, [[Kiamari Town]] and the [[Arabian Sea]] to the south and [[Lyari Town]] to the west. The majority of the population are [[Gujarati people|Gujarati]] and [[Sindhi people|Sindhi]] Muslims. Among the Gujarati-speaking people are trading communities such as [[Memon people|Memon]]s and [[Marwari people|Marwari]]s.<ref name=\"Dawn\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/150906|title=KARACHI: Saddar: the VIP town|date=5 August 2005|publisher=Dawn (newspaper)|accessdate=7 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nSaddar Town contained much of the oldest parts of Karachi.  The federal government under [[Pervez Musharraf]], who seized power in a [[1999 Pakistani coup d'\u00e9tat|1999 coup d'etat]], introduced local government reforms in the year 2000, which eliminated the previous \"third tier of government\" ([[Divisions of Pakistan|administrative divisions]]) and replaced it with the fourth tier ([[Districts of Pakistan|districts]]). The effect in Karachi was the dissolution of the former [[Karachi Division]], and the merging of its five districts to form a new Karachi City-District with eighteen autonomous constituent towns including Saddar Town. In 2011, the system was disbanded but remained in place for bureaucratic administration until 2015, when the [[Karachi Metropolitan Corporation]] system was reintroduced. In 2015, Saddar Town was re-organized as part of [[Karachi South]].\n\n== Neighbourhoods ==\nSaddar Town was made up of the following:\n\n{|cellspacing=\"6\"\n|-\n|\n* [[Bath Island]]\n* [[Clifton (Karachi)|Clifton]]\n* [[City Railway Colony]]\n* [[Civil Lines]]\n* [[Garden (Karachi)|Garden]]<ref name=Dawn/>\n* [[Gazdarabad]]\n* [[Islam Pura]]\n* [[Kalakot]]\n* [[Kehkashan]]\n* [[Kharadar]]<ref name=Dawn/>\n|\n* [[Ghanchi Para]]<ref name=Dawn/>\n* [[Millat Nagar]]\n* [[Nanak Wara]]<ref name=Dawn/>\n* [[Narayan Pura]]\n* [[Old Haji Camp]]\n* [[Ranchore Line]]\n* [[Saddar]]\n* Staff Lines Cantt\n* Iqbal Lines Cantt\n* Army Officers Mess\n* Jinnah Lines Cantt\n* Umerkot Lines Cantt\n* Askari-I Cantt\n* Askari-II Cantt\n* Askari-III Cantt\n* Com Kar Cantt\n* Abdul Sattar Edhi Hockey Stadium Cantt\n* [[Shah Rasool Colony]]\n* [[Sikanderabad (Karachi)|Sikanderabad]]\n* [[Shireen Jinnah Colony]]\n|}\n\n<gallery>\n</gallery>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[City District Government]]\n* [[Karachi]]\n* [[Lahore]]\n*[[Sindh Baloch Cooperative Housing Society]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.karachicity.gov.pk Karachi Website]\n* [https://archive.is/20121128182904/http://14.192.147.139/cdgk/Home/Towns/GulshanTown/tabid/211/townid/6/default.aspx Saddar Town]\n\n\n\n{{Karachi Towns}}\n{{Karachi topics}}\n\n{{coord|24|51|27|N|67|00|10|E|region:PK_type:city_source:kolossus-ruwiki|display=title}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Saddar Town}}\n[[Category:Saddar Town| ]]\n